<b>Siege Preparation - Walls</b>: <br> The main defense of your city are the walls separating the enemy scimitars from your throat. As everyone knows, the outer walls of the city, built by the Emperor Theodosius in the 5th century, are the greatest, most impressive piece of siege architecture in the whole of Europe. The only time these walls have been breached, was during the sack of the city in 1204 by the Frankish crusaders. If these walls would fall, the second line of defence would be the Constantinian walls, which have been abandoned for a long time and in their current condition could not stop even a determined beggar. Finally, the core of the city is defended by the final line of Severan walls, which are also crumbling and haven't been properly maintained for centuries. In order to prepare for the siege, we need to restore our once glorious fortifications. How shall we focus on their reconstruction? <br> <br> \[Explanation: Enemy will attempt to tear down your walls. When the integrity of the current wall closest to the enemy is low enough, they will assault them. After they take the outer wall, they will start attacking the next one in line. The walls are not identical and have different defence bonuses. If the enemy would successfully breach all the three walls - Theodosian, Constantinian and Severan, after the final assault you will lose the game. Do not let this happen, Empire must not be allowed to perish!\]
-> The Theodosian Wall is the first and strongest line of defence, it needs to be repaired - this is the highest priority. \[Materials -60\] 
    Theodosian Wall is the longest and strongest of City's fortifications, stretching for 3.5 miles from the North to the South. The battle for our lives will be won or lost on its battlements, so you order its full reconstruction. <br> \[Materials -60\]  <br> \[Theodosian Wall is restored to 100%\]
    <<ChangeFraction fOuterWall 1>>   
    <<Change iMaterials -60>> 
-> The Constantinian Wall hasn't seen combat for a thousand years and is in a really bad shape. However, it will be vital if the outer wall is breached. It must be rebuilt. \[Materials -160\] 
    Constantinian Wall is barely more than a ruin and for the past few centuries has mostly served a source of bricks for the town people. However, with our efforts, it is now restored and we have a secondary line of defence to fall back to. <br> \[Materials -160\] <br> \[Constantinian Wall is restored to 100%\]
    <<ChangeFraction fMiddleWall 1>>   
