</b> Ottomans use prisoners to fill the Moat </b> <br> The moat protecting the Theodosian Walls is a serious issue for the Ottoman war machine and they have to deal with it before they can hope to breach the walls themselves. <br>Unfortunately, Ottomans have managed to capture enough prisoners, primarily refugees from the countryside, some slaves and soldiers captured in the skirmishes to form a labour detachment a few thousands strong, which they are sending now towards the walls. <br> Ottoman state is run with a whip and brutal discipline – even their elite Janissaries are slave-soldiers, so there is no mercy to be expected, their plan is clear. Turks are herding the prisoners towards the moat and will force them to fill it with earth or their own bodies, both options acceptable. <br> You hear your soldiers murmuring atop the walls – the archers anxiously play with arrows in their quivers, waiting for your orders. It is one thing to shoot at the invaders, but entirely another to shoot at your own countrymen, taken prisoner and forced to labour on the enemy’s behalf. Your siege commander turns to you. <br> “Emperor, we cannot let the moat be filled. God forgive us, but we need to order our archers to fire on the enslaved labourers, otherwise we will all soon be slaves. What are your orders?”
