 Your command echoes across the walls, and reluctantly, your archers draw their bows. The first volleys rain down upon the enslaved prisoners, a brutal decision made in the face of strategic necessity. The moat is protected, but the atmosphere atop the walls turns dark. The morale of your troops falls, but you try to convince yourself that this sacrifice was necessary.
